                    About this Guide     This Guide is intended to provide assistance with APA, MLA, AMA, ICMJE, and Chicago styles.  The Guide provides links to the basic information you need to know when using these formats for your bibliography.  Note that the information listed here should not be used as a substitute for consulting with the official style guide manuals.  UIC Library will have copies of the style guides and writing manuals in their reference or reserve collections.           Citation Management Tools     For help with using citation manager software such as RefWorks and EndNote, please see the RefWorks, EndNote, and Reference Manager guide.     RefWorks and Other Citation Management Tools   by Rebecca Raszewski   Last Updated Mar 20, 2020  3798 views this year           DOI Help     For many citation styles, DOIs (digital object identifiers) are used.  The following resources will help in working with DOIs.     DOI Lookup    more...  less...   This tool will look up a DOI if you have information about the source.     DOI Resolver    more...  less...   If you have a DOI, this link will bring you to the article the DOI references.           Writing & Style Guide Web Sites      Grammar Handbook from UIUC  Grammar and writing tips.    OWL at Purdue  Sections on each part of the writing process, such as thesis statement, outline, etc. Includes recommendations on APA, MLA, and Chicago style.           UIC Writing Center                 Writing is one of the most
    important skills that students take away from college. To help students
    learn about writing, UIC offers a special free resource, a peer writing
    center, where students work with other students to improve as writers.        UIC Writing Center               Next: APA Style >>          Last Updated:  Apr 21, 2020 8:30 AM    URL:  https://researchguides.uic.edu/styleguides    Print Page     Staff Login        Subjects:  Writing, Style & Citations    Tags:  ama , apa , chicago style , chicago_lhs , chicago_lhs_feature , daley , icmje , mla , peoria_lhs , rockford_lhs , turabian , urbana_lhs                   Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations          Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Phone  (312) 996-2724              Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago    1750 W. Polk St.   Chicago , IL  60612       Circulation  (312) 996-8966    Reference  (312) 996-9163              Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria    One Illini Drive PO Box 1649   Peoria , IL  61656       Phone  (309) 671-8490              Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford    1601 Parkview Ave.   Rockford , IL  61107       Phone  (815) 395-5650              Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana    102 Medical Sciences Building, 506 S. Mathews   Urbana , IL  61801       Circulation  (217) 333-4893    Reference  (217) 244-0607             Faculty services    Alumni services    Distance student services    Accessibility services     Social Networking             © 2016 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois  Privacy Policy    Campus Links   University of Illinois  Chicago  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield         Chat with a Librarian  Close           